# Bartleby environment variables.
#
# VITE_DROPBOX_APP_KEY — your Dropbox app's "App key" from the App Console
#   (https://www.dropbox.com/developers/apps).
#
#   The VITE_ prefix is CORRECT AND INTENTIONAL here, and is the one documented
#   exception to the "never VITE_ an API key" rule:
#
#   Bartleby uses the OAuth 2 PKCE flow, in which the app key is a PUBLIC CLIENT
#   IDENTIFIER, not a secret. PKCE exists precisely so that public clients can
#   do OAuth without a secret — a per-request code_verifier proves the caller's
#   legitimacy instead. The app key is visible in every OAuth redirect URL by
#   design, so shipping it in the bundle discloses nothing.
#
#   Your Dropbox APP SECRET is a real secret. It is NOT used by this app and
#   must never appear in any VITE_ variable, in a committed .env, or anywhere
#   in client-side code.
#
# Set this locally in `.env`, and in the Netlify dashboard
# (Site settings → Environment variables) for production builds.
VITE_DROPBOX_APP_KEY=your_dropbox_app_key_here

# Required redirect URIs — add BOTH to your Dropbox app's "Redirect URIs" list:
#   http://localhost:5173/                 (local dev; http is allowed on localhost)
#   https://bartleby-scriv.netlify.app/    (production)
# They must match byte-for-byte, trailing slash included.
